                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260406-240-off1299 t18260406-240-crimeloc1302"></join>. On the 27th of March, about seven o'clock in the evening I saw the prisoner looking into his shop; there was a pair of steps at the window to keep the people from the paint - they were open, he closed them, and put them under the window - he then went a little way, returned, and took them up, and put them down again - then took them up and went away - I secured him.</p>
